# The Remainders

The remainders of the postage stamps have an interesting story of their own. In May, 1862, the Superintendent of Finanace at Bologna wrote to the Director General of Posts, Ministry of Public Works, Turin to inform him that he had in his care a large number of unsold stamps, together with a number of metal clich\'es which had been using in printing the stamps and ask for instructions as to what to do with them.

